{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how test coverage split between parent and child 568c will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fcac7738352b67417"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"test coverage split between parent and child 568c"},{"coaching":"Pin down operator tooling for downgrade-window affected-ID capture with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fadaa6f46bc524fad"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"operator tooling for downgrade-window affected-ID capture"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":0,"dropped":11,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":13899,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":14,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":3491,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":5709},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":260.1,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":677132.6,"total_ms":677522.5,"verify_requests":24},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile 'skip' (Architecture Decisions) with 'refuse' (AC4): state explicitly whether `process_edit` silently drops `creation_channel`/`creation_channel_inferred` fields from EDIT payloads or raises/logs an error, and update both sections to use the same verb.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Architecture Decisions: 'make process_edit skip those names before its generic state assignment'","AC4: 'process_edit plus every specialized mutation processor refuse to overwrite creation_channel or creation_channel_inferred after genesis'","These two verbs ('skip' vs 'refuse') describe different observable behaviors: silent discard vs. raised error/logged warning."],"finding":"The Architecture Decisions section says `process_edit` will 'skip those names before its generic state assignment', but AC4 says the processors will 'refuse to overwrite' — 'skip' (silent drop) and 'refuse' (error/exception) are materially different behaviors that affect observability, error handling, and downstream debugging. An executor cannot determine which behavior to implement without clarification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4550dc4ca20c669a","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS' paragraph; Acceptance Criteria — AC4","norm_id":"nce5f5b5ed8522606","priority":0.536,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor implementing a silent skip passes the AC4 pytest test (field not overwritten) but leaves no trace when a caller mistakenly sends creation_channel in an EDIT payload.","An executor implementing a raise/log satisfies the 'refuse' language but could break callers that currently pass unknown keys."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"State the default in the Architecture Decisions paragraph: e.g., 'process_edit silently skips (drops without error) any key in _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS; callers supplying those keys receive no exception.' Then update AC4 to say 'silently ignore' rather than 'refuse to overwrite', or vice-versa if an explicit error is intended.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] 568c must ensure test_creation_channel_compaction.py contains test functions whose IDs include `legacy_snapshot` and `snapshot_only` (or update parent AC10's proof command to reference the actual test locations and selectors used).","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC10: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only or horizon or rebuild\" tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py'","568c AC1 uses -k recorded (covers SNAPSHOT-only replay for recorded channels, not -k snapshot_only)","568c AC2 uses -k inferred (covers SNAPSHOT-only replay for inferred channels, not -k snapshot_only)","568c AC3 uses test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel (covers legacy-snapshot behavior in a different file, not test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k legacy_snapshot)","568c AC5 uses -k 'rebuild or horizon or rollback_recovery' (covers rebuild and horizon but not legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only)","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC10's proof command specifies `test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k \"legacy_snapshot or snapshot_only or horizon or rebuild\"`, but child 568c routes legacy-snapshot behavior to `test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel` (AC3, a different file) and subsumes SNAPSHOT-only replay under `-k recorded` and `-k inferred` (ACs 1 and 2, different keywords). Unless 568c's implementation also creates test functions named to match `legacy_snapshot` and `snapshot_only` in `test_creation_channel_compaction.py`, the parent's completion verifier will silently collect zero results for those two keywords in that file, causing AC10 to appear unproven even though the behavior is tested elsewhere.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcac7738352b67417","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87, Acceptance Criteria AC1/AC2/AC3 vs. parent AC10 proof command","norm_id":"n8a019b62365b6696","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["The parent's final completion verifier runs the exact AC10 proof command; `test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k legacy_snapshot` finds zero tests because they are in test_reducer_snapshot.py; the criterion is falsely reported as uncovered.","A developer implementing 568c writes SNAPSHOT-only replay tests under the `recorded` and `inferred` selectors with no `snapshot_only`-named function; the parent completion check passes on horizon/rebuild but silently skips legacy_snapshot and snapshot_only."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In 568c, add explicit `legacy_snapshot`-named tests to `test_creation_channel_compaction.py` (e.g., `test_legacy_snapshot_jira_inference`, `test_legacy_snapshot_unknown_fallback`) and rename or alias the SNAPSHOT-only replay assertions to include `snapshot_only` in their function names. Alternatively, revise parent AC10's proof command to replace `-k legacy_snapshot` with `-k creation_channel` on `test_reducer_snapshot.py` (its actual location per 568c AC3) and to replace `-k snapshot_only` with `-k \"recorded or inferred\"` where those tests live.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact fallback behavior when `process_edit` encounters a field name in `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS`: silent skip (current behavior generalized), warning log, or raised error; reconcile the 'skip' language in Architecture Decisions with the 'refuse' language in AC4.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py lines 492-504: `for field_name, new_value in fields.items(): if field_name not in state: continue ... state[field_name] = new_value`","Plan uses the word 'skip' (silent) while AC4 says processors 'refuse to overwrite' — these imply different behaviors (silent drop vs. active refusal/error)","No fallback behavior (warning, error, or silent drop) is specified for the case where an EDIT event supplies a value for an immutable field"],"finding":"The plan says `process_edit` will 'skip those names before its generic state assignment' for `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS`, but the existing `process_edit` guard is `if field_name not in state: continue` (silently skips fields absent from state). Once `process_create` seeds `creation_channel` into state, the field IS in state, so the existing guard does NOT protect it — any EDIT event carrying `creation_channel` would overwrite it. The plan introduces `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS` to fix this, but never specifies the fallback behavior when an EDIT event supplies the field: skip silently, log a warning, or raise an error.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fba32312d872acd18","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'define _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset({\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"}) and make process_edit skip those names before its generic state assignment'","norm_id":"n09b5c85fcb7f4cf5","priority":0.469,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An EDIT event with `creation_channel` in its fields dict silently loses the mutation (skip), which is correct but undetectable","An adversarial or buggy writer sends an EDIT with `creation_channel: cli` on a jira-origin ticket; the skip is silent and no audit trail records the attempted mutation"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify a concrete mechanism for capturing 'affected IDs' during a violated compaction-pause window (e.g., 'scan the compaction activity log / SNAPSHOT mtime for the downgrade window', or 'run `rebar compact --dry-run --since=<downgrade-ts>` to enumerate tickets compacted without creation_channel') so that the rebuild step can be applied exhaustively rather than relying on manual recall.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots'","No description of how 'affected IDs' are captured — no log query, no compaction audit trail, no tooling reference","DATA LOSS RISK: if the affected-ID list is incomplete, some tickets remain with provenance-stripped SNAPSHOTs indefinitely"],"finding":"The plan instructs operators to 'record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity' but provides no mechanism or tooling for reliably capturing that set; missed IDs would be silently left with provenance-stripped SNAPSHOTs — a DATA LOSS RISK for audit integrity.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fadaa6f46bc524fad","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix; AC — 'Story 568c adds a regression for that compensating-forward recovery'","norm_id":"na6cbfe322115620f","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator performs emergency downgrade; old binary compacts N tickets concurrently before the pause is applied; operator reconstructs only a partial list of affected IDs from memory or ad-hoc log search; remaining tickets are left with creation_channel-free SNAPSHOTs that the new binary cannot distinguish from legitimately-unknown tickets"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a pre-implementation empirical probe (e.g., a one-off script or fixture that samples real or representative anonymized legacy CREATE events) to validate that LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID exactly match all Jira-origin records and that no non-Jira records satisfy the three-signal predicate before finalizing the constants.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'require the exact three-signal Jira predicate and add near-miss negative cases' — prescribed tests are synthetic unit fixtures, not a measurement against real historical data","No spike, sample audit, or corpus measurement step is described anywhere in the plan","The plan asserts 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' — this is a reasoning-based claim about real historical corpus shape","The predicate depends on exact literal constants whose validity against actual stored event logs is unverified"],"finding":"The three-signal historical Jira inference predicate (ticket_id prefix + exact LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR + exact LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) is asserted safe against real historical records by reasoning alone, with no empirical probe or sample measurement against actual legacy event logs to confirm the predicate produces no false positives or unexpected false negatives at corpus scale.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f425e6ee4033fa6de","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree…'; Risks — 'False historical attribution'","norm_id":"n34f45e11947917c4","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A legacy CREATE event was written with a variant author string (e.g., capitalization, whitespace, or a version-specific prefix) that does not match LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR exactly, causing a real Jira ticket to silently project unknown rather than jira","A non-Jira ticket coincidentally satisfies the three-signal predicate, producing a false jira attribution with creation_channel_inferred: true","The corpus contains both REBAR_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR variants for Jira-origin records, making the predicate coverage incomplete"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Before story e622 lands, run a read-only audit query (e.g., `rebar list --format ndjson | jq 'select(.event_type==\"CREATE\") | {id, author, env_id}'`) against a representative historical corpus and confirm the predicate covers all expected Jira-origin records with no unexpected matches. Record the sample result as a comment in _version.py alongside the constant definitions.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Justify the placement of the downgrade runbook in `docs/concurrency.md`, or relocate the three-state schema matrix and compaction-pause procedure to a more discoverable home (e.g., `docs/operations.md` or a dedicated `docs/schema-rollback.md`) and update the AC proof commands accordingly.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"docs/concurrency.md defines the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix, the unconditional compaction pause, the affected-ID capture step, plus compensating-forward rebuild from retained .retired CREATE files.\"","No rationale is given in the plan for locating schema-rollback runbook content in a file named 'concurrency'.","ABSENCE: no pointer from docs/concurrency.md to an operations or deployment guide, and no mention of whether an existing operations/deployment doc already exists that would be a more natural home."],"finding":"The plan places the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix, compaction pause procedure, affected-ID capture step, and compensating-forward rebuild instructions in `docs/concurrency.md`, but no rationale is given for this placement. 'Concurrency' conventionally describes concurrent-access semantics, not schema rollback/downgrade runbooks. Operators and auditors looking for downgrade procedures are unlikely to search there, reducing the operational value of the otherwise well-specified rollback path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2c0d882f9244379a","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — last two AC bullets; Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix paragraph","norm_id":"ndb06f32775a3ee59","priority":0.0943,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator performing an emergency downgrade searches docs/operations.md or docs/deployment.md (natural homes for runbook content) and misses the compaction-pause instruction, violating the pause and triggering the attribution-loss scenario the plan describes.","A new maintainer auditing the rollback procedure reads docs/concurrency.md and conflates schema-downgrade guidance with concurrent-writer semantics, causing confusion about scope."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section documenting the creation-channel provenance architectural decisions: the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS reducer guard pattern, the late-import convention for cross-package constants, the closed-vocabulary rationale, and the inference-marker trust boundary.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["No ADR file (e.g., docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md) or CLAUDE.md section is mentioned anywhere in the plan","The plan introduces two novel patterns: a named immutability guard in the reducer and a deliberate cross-package late-import; both require future contributors to know the constraint and the rationale","Documentation ACs target only existing markdown files and make lint, not a new ADR or CLAUDE.md entry","'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update' is the T5e documentation sub-check"],"finding":"The novel reducer guard pattern (_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS in process_edit) and the cross-component late-import convention (inbound_translate importing from rebar.reducer._version) are not captured in an ADR or CLAUDE.md entry — only existing documentation files are updated — leaving future contributors without a discoverable record of why these patterns were chosen and what constraints govern extending them.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4df1da3021d868ab","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — '_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS = frozenset…'; 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import … following the module's established late-import pattern'; Scope — documentation updates target docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, docs/concurrency.md","norm_id":"nea41a8a742d89bb3","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future contributor adds a new field to process_edit without knowing the _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS guard pattern exists, inadvertently making a different CREATE-only field mutable","A future reconciler module author adds a top-level import from rebar.reducer._version without understanding the late-import contract, causing a circular import regression","The closed-vocabulary rationale is not discoverable, so a future ingress author adds an ad-hoc string channel value outside the validator"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md (or add a section to CLAUDE.md) capturing: (1) why creation_channel is CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only and how _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS enforces it, (2) the late-import pattern rationale in inbound_translate, (3) the closed enum extension policy, and (4) the inference marker's diagnostic-only (non-security) trust boundary. Reference this ADR from the relevant AC.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define a staged rollout path (e.g., a feature flag or explicit operator gate) so the new creation_channel writes can be enabled incrementally, OR document and test the exact rollback procedure (including the compaction-pause enforcement mechanism) as a first-class tested AC item — the current AC for docs/concurrency.md covers documentation but does not include a behavioral test of the pause enforcement or a smoke-test of the full rollback sequence.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode; attribution defects are recovered by pausing the affected creation ingress at the deployment boundary and rolling forward.\"","\"If that pause is violated, record affected IDs from the downgrade-window compaction activity, re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired\"","The plan acknowledges scheduled compaction operations ('stop every scheduled or manual rebar compact invocation'), confirming this is a deployed system with operational cadence."],"finding":"The plan explicitly adopts a single-binary-flip deployment with no staged rollout flag or canary path, and the rollback procedure is non-trivial (requires operator action to stop compaction, capture affected IDs, re-deploy, and rebuild snapshots) — failing T12(a) and making T12(b) only partially satisfied for a system with scheduled compaction operations.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a0437a310680f31","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — 'Downgrade first-compaction omission'; AC — docs/concurrency.md item","norm_id":"nf300c04e49cea96a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator deploys the new binary to a system with active scheduled compaction before verifying the pause is in place; the compaction pause is violated during a rollback window, producing SNAPSHOTs that omit creation_channel, requiring a non-trivial multi-step recovery.","A team with multiple deployment targets (e.g., CI runner + developer workstations) cannot gate the change to a subset of traffic without a feature flag."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add an AC item that tests the rollback recovery sequence end-to-end: deploy new binary, write some CREATE events, simulate a compaction-pause violation (run old-binary compaction), re-deploy new binary, call rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log, and assert creation_channel is correctly restored. This converts the documented three-state matrix into a tested, cheap rollback path. Alternatively, add a REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_ENABLED environment flag so the new field can be deployed to a subset of processes before enabling writes universally.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly state that `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` is idempotent per ticket (safe to re-run on an already-rebuilt SNAPSHOT) and describe how a partially-completed multi-ticket rebuild can be resumed without double-applying or skipping any ticket (e.g., by checking whether the SNAPSHOT already contains a non-unknown `creation_channel` before rebuilding).","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'re-deploy the new binary, and rebuild those snapshots from the full log with rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log/include_retired'","'Story 568c adds a regression for that compensating-forward recovery'","No mention of idempotency or partial-restart safety for the rebuild across multiple tickets"],"finding":"The compensating-forward rebuild step (`rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` over 'affected IDs') is the sole stated recovery path after a violated compaction-pause, but the plan never asserts this operation is idempotent or resumable if interrupted mid-run across a large set of tickets.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f95809d484a03e983","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix; Risks and Mitigations — 'Downgrade first-compaction omission'","norm_id":"n2e42477cab322fa6","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":["A large deployment with thousands of tickets undergoes a violated compaction pause; the rebuild run crashes partway through; re-running it either reprocesses already-fixed tickets (harmless only if idempotent) or skips them (losing provenance for a subset)"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence in the rollback matrix section: 'rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log is idempotent: if a SNAPSHOT already reflects a non-unknown creation_channel derived from the retained CREATE, the rebuild is a no-op for that ticket, making a partial-run safe to restart without tracking per-ticket completion state.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify that `_project_legacy_creation_channel` is a REDUCER-side projection function (called from within the `process_create` or `_replay` path), not placed inside `inbound_translate._event_meta` (a write-side event-metadata factory); update the Architecture Decisions section to name the correct read-side host module and call site.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py lines 158-168: `def _event_meta() -> tuple[int, str, str, str]: ... return (_time.time_ns(), str(_uuid.uuid4()), _rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler'), _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler'))`","Plan states: 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import ... following the module's established late-import pattern' — but the existing late-import pattern in _event_meta is for `time` and `uuid` only (write-side concerns)","Legacy Jira inference is a reducer projection concern (read-side), not a write-side concern — it evaluates existing stored events, not new ones being written"],"finding":"The plan assigns `_project_legacy_creation_channel` (a reducer read-side decision rule) to `inbound_translate._event_meta`, which is confirmed by code inspection to be a write-side factory function that returns (timestamp_ns, uuid4_str, env_id, author) for new events. The late-import pattern cited ('following the module's established late-import pattern') in _event_meta refers to importing `time` and `uuid` — not reducer constants. Placing legacy inference logic inside a write-side helper is a structural mis-location that could cause the inference to run on the wrong side of the event boundary.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f736cf491d293c78b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section — 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import (from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) inside its function body'","norm_id":"n33bc9618bae82b50","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementor places `_project_legacy_creation_channel` inside `_event_meta`, which only runs during new event creation — legacy historical events are never re-evaluated by this path","The import `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` inside `_event_meta` creates a circular dependency risk (reconciler importing from rebar.reducer at write time rather than at read/reduce time)"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Place `_project_legacy_creation_channel` in `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (called from `process_create` when no concrete `creation_channel` is present) or `src/rebar/reducer/_replay.py`; the `inbound_translate._event_meta` sentence should be removed or replaced with a statement that the Jira inference runs in the reducer.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either add a `\"const\"` handler to `gen_types._pytype()` that emits `Literal[True]` for `{\"const\": true}`, or encode `creation_channel_inferred` as `{\"type\": \"boolean\", \"enum\": [true]}` so the existing `enum` handler fires; document the chosen approach in the Architecture Decisions.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/schemas/gen_types.py lines 115-149: `_pytype()` handles `$ref`, `enum`, array, object, scalar — no `const` branch; `jtype is None` returns `Any`","Plan states the schema encoding is `{\"const\": true}` and that the gen_types check must pass","The `--check` command only verifies the generated file matches re-generation output — it does NOT verify the generated type is semantically `Literal[True]`; it would pass with `Any`"],"finding":"The plan encodes `creation_channel_inferred` as `{\"const\": true}` in `ticket_state.schema.json` and asserts `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check` will pass (AC7), but `gen_types._pytype()` has no handler for the `\"const\"` keyword. Confirmed by reading `gen_types.py` lines 115-149: the method handles `$ref`, `enum`, array/object/scalar types — `const` falls through to the `jtype is None` branch returning `Any`. The generated type for `creation_channel_inferred` would be `NotRequired[Any]` rather than `NotRequired[Literal[True]]`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f55f0f2f91f1bb6d1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'ticket_state.schema.json encodes that rule formally as {\"const\": true}'; AC7 — 'Prove with ... python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","norm_id":"na6e816bbed667d5e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["gen_types regenerates types.py with `creation_channel_inferred: NotRequired[Any]` instead of `NotRequired[Literal[True]]`; the --check AC passes because the generated output matches the stale file","Type-checkers and consumers receive `Any` for the inference marker, defeating its diagnostic value"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `gen_types._pytype()`, add before the `jtype = node.get('type')` line: `if 'const' in node: self._used_typing.add('Literal'); return f\"Literal[{node['const']!r}]\"`. Alternatively, encode the schema field as `{\"enum\": [true]}` to reuse the existing `enum` branch.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Make the Architecture Decisions section explicit that 'written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' means 'the stored author or env_id value does not equal LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR or LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID respectively' — not a runtime env-var check — and that this falls out naturally from the three-signal predicate failing.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py lines 166-167: `_rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler'), _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler')` — default values are 'reconciler', same as LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID","Plan does not define 'written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' — the stored event author/env_id would equal whatever the env var was set to at write time, not a flag that the var was overridden","If REBAR_AUTHOR was overridden to 'reconciler' (the default), the event is indistinguishable from a default-written event; if overridden to something else, the three-signal predicate fails on the author check — but the plan never makes this chain explicit"],"finding":"The plan states 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' but never specifies what REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID override values trigger the `unknown` branch versus the three-signal `jira` inference. The env vars have a default of 'reconciler' (confirmed from `inbound_translate.py` line 166-167), making them coincide with `LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR`/`LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID`. The plan does not define when a non-default env-var override counts as a disqualifying signal.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc2702e81a6a684b5","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown'","norm_id":"n29767ff50cd0eca0","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A deployment sets REBAR_AUTHOR=custom-reconciler; historical events written then have author='custom-reconciler', which fails the LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR check and correctly projects unknown — but the plan's 'REBAR_AUTHOR override' language is opaque about this being the mechanism","A future implementor adds a check for whether REBAR_AUTHOR was explicitly set, rather than checking the stored author value, and produces the wrong result"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace 'legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides' with 'legacy events whose stored author ≠ LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR or stored env_id ≠ LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID' to make the decision rule self-contained and unambiguous.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] At least one child (preferably 6fe2 as the foundation story or e622 as the documentation story) must explicitly assign writing a paragraph in docs/event-schema.md or docs/output-schemas.md that states creation_channel is additive to, not a replacement for, the actor and env_id provenance dimensions.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC13: 'docs/event-schema.md plus docs/output-schemas.md define ... the distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance'","6fe2 Files: docs/event-schema.md for 'CREATE channel contract' — no mention of actor/env distinction","e622 What: 'Document recorded versus inferred Jira provenance, the import/source_* distinction, and the diagnostic trust boundary' — covers source_* but not actor/env","568c AC7: 'verify docs/event-schema.md plus docs/output-schemas.md jointly cover ... actor/environment/source_* distinctions' — verify only, not write","No child's What or Files section explicitly assigns writing 'creation_channel is distinct from actor/environment/env_id provenance' to a deliverable","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"The documentation requirement in parent AC13 — 'the distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance' — has no child that explicitly owns *writing* this content. 6fe2 documents the local channel contract (CREATE semantics), e622 documents the import/source_* distinction and Jira provenance, and 568c's AC7 *verifies* the union via test_schema_coverage.py. The actor/environment half of the distinction ('creation_channel is additive to actor and env_id, not a replacement') is not assigned as a writing task in any child's What section, Files list, or individual ACs.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f86ba38abe2fd579c","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 docs/event-schema.md scope; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 docs/output-schemas.md scope; child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 AC7","norm_id":"n45ff2f404ad31b22","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["test_schema_coverage.py checks for a prose assertion that creation_channel does not replace actor or env_id; neither 6fe2 nor e622 has written it; 568c's AC7 runs the coverage test and fails; no child owns the fix.","An auditor reading docs/event-schema.md finds channel vocabulary and import semantics but no explanation of why actor/env_id are not sufficient — the parent's stated rationale for the feature is missing from documentation."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to 6fe2's What section and docs/event-schema.md scope: 'Add a paragraph stating that creation_channel is additive to actor and env_id — it records which interface created the ticket, whereas actor identifies the human or system and env_id identifies the environment. This preserves the existing actor/environment provenance model unchanged.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] e622 should explicitly state which function-level changes from 6fe2 it builds upon in _processors.py (e.g., '_project_legacy_creation_channel is appended after the provisional-unknown assignment from 6fe2; _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS is preserved unchanged'), and 568c should do the same for e622's additions.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["6fe2 Files: 'src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: CREATE projection, provisional legacy default, and explicit EDIT immutability guard'","e622 Files: 'src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: shared deterministic legacy projection helper'","568c Files: 'src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: post-SNAPSHOT legacy projection using the shared helper'","Neither e622 nor 568c states 'I assume 6fe2 has delivered _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS at this location' or pins the exact call ordering within process_create","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"All three children modify `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` without specifying the expected merged state that each subsequent child assumes. 6fe2 adds `_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS` and provisional-unknown logic inside `process_create`; e622 then adds `_project_legacy_creation_channel` definition and its `process_create` call-site to the same function; 568c adds a `process_snapshot` call-site. No child specifies the exact post-merge function signatures or insertion points within `process_create` that the next implementer should assume, leaving implicit shared state across the sequential integration.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f45b028c2e9aab495","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 Files; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 Files; child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 Files — all list src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py","norm_id":"n392b55cf6523f5c7","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["e622's implementer, working from the e622 spec alone, rewrites the provisional-unknown block from 6fe2 rather than appending to it, dropping _IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS or reversing the call order within process_create.","568c's implementer finds that process_create's state after both 6fe2 and e622 integration differs from their assumption, causing _project_legacy_creation_channel to be called before recorded CREATE data is folded."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a short 'Assumed baseline from 6fe2 / e622' subsection to the Approach Rationale or Files section of e622 and 568c respectively, naming the exact symbols (_IMMUTABLE_EDIT_FIELDS, provisional-unknown assignment, _project_legacy_creation_channel call in process_create) that must be present and must not be overwritten.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan asserts creation_channel is immutable after genesis ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'), but the existing process_edit in _processors.py applies any field already in state when it appears in EDIT.fields (line 494: `if field_name not in state: continue`). Since process_create will add creation_channel (and conditionally creation_channel_inferred) to state, a subsequent EDIT event containing fields.creation_channel will silently overwrite genesis provenance. The plan never specifies that process_edit must have an explicit named exclusion for these keys — only that mutation events 'ignore the key', which is true for specialized processors (LINK, STATUS, JIRA_BIND) but is NOT automatically true for the general-purpose process_edit without an explicit guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2bb5fda9fe912bdd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section ('Reducer processors treat creation_channel as CREATE/SNAPSHOT-only state and ignore the key on every later mutation event'); src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py lines 485-510","norm_id":"n4289d61664b4bf81","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In _processors.py, add a module-level frozenset: `_IMMUTABLE_FIELDS = frozenset({'creation_channel', 'creation_channel_inferred'})` and add `if field_name in _IMMUTABLE_FIELDS: continue` inside the process_edit loop before the general assignment. Reference this constant from the plan's Architecture Decisions section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G4","G3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"Child 6fe2 AC4 claims that 'a legacy CREATE with no channel reduces to unknown without creation_channel_inferred,' implying the reducer writes creation_channel=unknown into compiled state. Child e622 defines _project_legacy_creation_channel as 'a no-op when state already has creation_channel.' If 6fe2's reducer sets creation_channel=unknown for missing-field legacy CREATEs, e622's helper will always be a no-op for those records, blocking Jira inference from ever firing on full-log replay. The two children cannot both be correct as written: either 6fe2 sets unknown (which blocks e622's inference) or 6fe2 leaves the field absent (which means 6fe2 AC4's 'reduces to unknown' is not verifiable at 6fe2's own delivery boundary, before e622 exists).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f93e1c06c2f62b2e4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 AC4; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What (_project_legacy_creation_channel no-op guard)","norm_id":"nae1fde64f234f78e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Define the contract explicitly: 6fe2's reducer does NOT write creation_channel into compiled_state when the CREATE event has no creation_channel field (i.e., field remains absent from state dict). e622's _project_legacy_creation_channel is the sole writer for legacy records (setting jira+inferred on match, unknown on mismatch). Update 6fe2 AC4 to say 'a legacy CREATE with no channel is left without creation_channel until the inference helper runs, which then projects unknown for non-Jira records without an inferred marker.' This keeps the no-op guard meaningful (it guards against re-inference of already-resolved state, including recorded channels and post-e622 unknown outputs).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"7b1bd8ff567a87e1","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":260.1,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":677132.6,"total_ms":677522.5,"verify_requests":24},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"faa40e7b07b1ebfd7f0a12e122e9017b0cdd0b35"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784267997609747001,"uuid":"038fecce-4bad-4c88-be8b-668ed14ce58a"}